BETWEEN MAY 31 AND JUNE 1, 1984, THE PRIVATE PILOT IS BELIEVED TO HAVE DRIVEN TO 
THE AIRPORT, PARKED HIS CAR, AND BOARDED HIS AIRCRAFT FOR A PRESUMED 
PERSONAL FLIGHT. THE PILOT'S WIFE BECAME CONCERNED ABOUT HER HUSBAND'S 
FAILURE TO APPEAR AT WORK, AND SHE NOTIFIED LOCAL AUTHORITIES THAT HER 
HUSBAND WAS MISSING. THE NTSB FIRST LEARNED OF THE MISSING AIRCRAFT ON 
JUNE 19, 1984. AS OF JUNE 14, 1985, NEITHER THE FREMONT POLICE DEPT., NOR THE 
NTSB HAS LEARNED OF THE AIRCRAFT AND PILOT'S LOCATION. 
